message:
Last, but not least, to be introduced is our communications nerd. Also big on coffee, hiking and U.S politics. Meet Hanna: 

"My whole life's been about creating meaning. I'd like to think it benefits me as a person as well as society as a whole. Today I have a dream job at this Swedish startup TRINE, where we work with financing solar energy in emerging markets. And is it one thing the startup-community has taught me it's the strong sense of believing in people's potential, not only focusing on what they've done or who they are but also where they are going and who they want to be. 

Diversity is not only right, it's smart. This insight is something I want to influence everything I do, every decision I take. Why? Because it makes us better. 

As far as I can remember I've always valued people coming together as the most important part of making a society unified, open and compassionate. I think people meeting each other is the key for respect and understanding. That's what made me so keen on joining Hello Neighbour, because I think sometimes we make all of this way to complicated. 

We have this strong belief that we will never be able to handle this. It's like we think we are destined to be apart, that we are so far away from each other that we can never be united. In reality we are so much more alike than we think. In the end the real obstacle is that we are so deep into our own social circles, that we barely meet new people if not forced to. 

The consequence? We miss out on so many new friends, competence and ideas. I hope Project Unify can contribute to making it easier for people to come together. That in reality it might not be more complicated to meet new people than saying: Hello - from the other side. 

I mean, let's start there. Or over a "Fika"."
story: Project Unify with Hanna Lindquist at Sardinia Bay Nature Reserve.

message:
Next out to be introduced is our very own engineer and one of the founders of Project Unify, Anton: 

"I would like to see myself as a person with a big heart and a lot of humor. I love making people laugh and being around positive, initiative people. I spend my spare time with my love, my friends, my gangsta dog Murphy Brown and watching/playing football (MUFC of course). Apart from these lovely ways of spending time I‚Äôm a big fan of science, environmental- and social issues and sometimes I enjoy a fine smoky whiskey to relax after long days. 

I am an energy engineer and I‚Äôm currently working as a Project Manager. Project Unify is a mission; it is a responsibility and a really important step towards the vision of uniting for a better future. Me and my friend Nawar Hermiz started this project out after putting our heads together and focusing on what we could do to be a part of a solution for better integration. It was a bit of a coincidence, though sometimes that‚Äôs what‚Äôs needed. I have since been working hard to spread our organisation. I always aim high. 

I love challenges and this is one of the biggest challenges in our lifetime. Let‚Äôs work this out together. We can solve big problems by working alongside each other.  Let‚Äôs unite."
name: Timeline Photos

message:
Next up is our tech-genius, or at least soon-to-be. We'll probably have to prepare for saying goodbye to her when she's off to Google, Spotify or Facebook. Let's introduce Amanda: 

"Hello world! I am a software engineer student. Yes, I like solving things. Riddles, puzzles, ingenious wordplays and social issues. That is why I‚Äôm a part of Project Unify. I believe people should be connected and integrated with each other, not divided and segregated. I believe that we as humans, by our every day actions are the ones who can make the big change. With project Unify I can be a part of that change, and hopefully help and inspire you and others to do the same.

Apart from solving things, I cannot live without high mountain peeks and pitch black coffee. My big dream is to climb at least one mountain of every continent. I have seen the sun rise from the roof of Africa, now only the rest of the world awaits. 

Until then, I will be enjoying my Java."

message:
Hey, y'all! 

Don't miss this incredible article by Erik Niva. It's basically a rebuttal to those who says it's impossible and too hard to get people with different backgrounds to meet. Well, turns out that all you need is some soccer, compassion and openness. 

If we can see people coming together as an opportunity rather than an obstacle we could move mountains, reach the moon and change the world.

message:
Second out is our global mastermind with a burning engagement in Human Rights, Emina: 

"I'm 24 years old and one of the team members in Project Unify. I live and study in Gothenburg and where my major is Masters program in Human Rights.
 
I got in contact with my team through a project called HelloNeighbour that was initiated by BlackDot and it was during this project that we created our idea. I was lucky to meet this team because at the end of the day we wanted the same thing, to bring people together.
 
I choose to be a part of Project Unify because I want to help people, people who feel left out of society and want to make more of their lives. By helping them to come in contact with the society they get an opportunity to evolve and become a part of a new society where they can feel like home. My passion is to help people in everyway I can. By doing this with people who has the same passion and urge to accomplish this I think we can succeed in bringing people together."
name: Timeline Photos

message:
It's time for y'all to get to know the team. 
First out is one of the founders, Nawar: 

"So, who am I? I‚Äôm Nawar. I can‚Äôt sit still so I tend to move around from time to time. I usually like to plan the After Works, because I love to interact and meet new people. Currently I‚Äôm not working so I help out at the Red Cross as an interpreter. I'm an educated physiotherapist and I can give a kick-ass massage.   

A big smile is the most important in life. 
I keep a smile on my face whether it's when I'm acting or climbing ropes and bars while working out. If you can smile, your life is a success. 

Me and my friend Anton started Project Unify together because we wanted a change, but first and foremost to change. Everything started in Anton‚Äôs old car aka ‚Äúthe blueberry‚Äù, because it's blue and it looks like a blueberry. 

I hope that I can bring inspiration to my fellow humans with this idea and my vision is to see people coming closer together."
